# ============================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================

# This .gitignore is designed for MAXIMUM SECURITY
# for open source Android projects.
#
# Before making your repo public:
# 1. Review EVERY file being committed
# 2. Run: git status
# 3. Check for sensitive data: git log --all --full-history --source -- *secret*
# 4. If you accidentally committed secrets, use git-filter-repo to remove them
# 5. Rotate ALL compromised keys/passwords immediately
#
# Never commit:
# - IDE configuration files (.idea/, *.iml)
# - Keystore files (.jks, .keystore)
# - API keys
# - Passwords or tokens
# - Service account credentials
# - Database files with real data
# - User data or personal information
#
# For CI/CD secrets, use:
# - GitHub Secrets
# - GitLab CI/CD Variables
# - Environment variables
# - Secure secret management services
#
# If you need to share example configs, use:
# - .example files (e.g., config.properties.example)
# - Template files with placeholder values
# - Documentation explaining what values are needed